# Temporary media-worker AI waivers — reviewed 2026-07-02.
#
# Context:
# - The release gate still builds and imports the real AI runtime.
# - The product E2E gate exercises the full pipeline with AI enabled.
# - The fixed versions currently reported by Trivy are not installable from the
#   build index or are incompatible with the current FastAPI/MediaPipe/WhisperX
#   dependency graph.
#
# Compensating controls:
# - yt-dlp is used only for controlled public URL ingestion; the worker does not
#   expose arbitrary CLI flags such as --exec or --netrc-cmd.
# - The media-worker does not mount StaticFiles or accept public form uploads.
# - Hugging Face model loading is constrained by configured model names and does
#   not intentionally enable trust_remote_code.
#
# Remove these waivers when compatible fixed versions are available.
